
  <sn><md>### Metamorphic Rocks

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
Metamorphic rocks are rocks that have changed from their original form (igneous, sedimentary, or even older metamorphic rocks) due to **heat**, **pressure**, and **chemical activity** inside the Earth. This transformation occurs without melting, but minerals recrystallize and textures change, forming a new rock type.
